The paper also proposes and analyses different judgment aggregation rules, which involves mathematical and logical reasoning, making cs.LG (Logic in Computer Science) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper deals with properties of judgment aggregation rules, which can be seen as a problem in data structures (DS), making cs.DS a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the relation between judgment aggregation rules and voting rules, which can be seen as a problem in social choice theory (SI), making cs.SI a possible sub-category.
